{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_38","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"curl -L --fail --silent 'https://www.ebi.ac.uk/europepmc/webservices/rest/search?query=EXT_ID:27569046%20SRC:MED&format=json&pageSize=1&resultType=core'\"","aggregated_output":"{\"version\":\"6.9\",\"hitCount\":1,\"request\":{\"queryString\":\"EXT_ID:27569046 SRC:MED\",\"internalQuery\":\"EXT_ID:27569046 SRC:MED\",\"resultType\":\"CORE\",\"cursorMark\":\"*\",\"pageSize\":1,\"sort\":\"\",\"synonym\":false},\"resultList\":{\"result\":[{\"id\":\"27569046\",\"source\":\"MED\",\"pmid\":\"27569046\",\"doi\":\"10.1016/j.jmb.2016.08.023\",\"title\":\"3D Structure and Interaction of p24β and p24δ Golgi Dynamics Domains: Implication for p24 Complex Formation and Cargo Transport.\",\"authorString\":\"Nagae M, Hirata T, Morita-Matsumoto K, Theiler R, Fujita M, Kinoshita T, Yamaguchi Y.\",\"authorList\":{\"author\":[{\"fullName\":\"Nagae M\",\"firstName\":\"Masamichi\",\"lastName\":\"Nagae\",\"initials\":\"M\",\"authorId\":{\"type\":\"ORCID\",\"value\":\"0000-0002-5470-3807\"},\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Structural Glycobiology Team, Systems Glycobiology Research Group, RIKEN-Max Planck Joint Research Center, RIKEN Global Research Cluster, 2-1 Hirosawa, Wako City, Saitama 351-0198, Japan.\"}]}},{\"fullName\":\"Hirata T\",\"firstName\":\"Tetsuya\",\"lastName\":\"Hirata\",\"initials\":\"T\",\"authorId\":{\"type\":\"ORCID\",\"value\":\"0000-0003-1965-5405\"},\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Research Institute for Microbial Diseases and WPI Immunology Frontier Research Center, Osaka University, Suita, Osaka 565-0871, Japan.\"}]}},{\"fullName\":\"Morita-Matsumoto K\",\"firstName\":\"Kana\",\"lastName\":\"Morita-Matsumoto\",\"initials\":\"K\",\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Structural Glycobiology Team, Systems Glycobiology Research Group, RIKEN-Max Planck Joint Research Center, RIKEN Global Research Cluster, 2-1 Hirosawa, Wako City, Saitama 351-0198, Japan.\"}]}},{\"fullName\":\"Theiler R\",\"firstName\":\"Romina\",\"lastName\":\"Theiler\",\"initials\":\"R\",\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Research Institute for Microbial Diseases and WPI Immunology Frontier Research Center, Osaka University, Suita, Osaka 565-0871, Japan.\"}]}},{\"fullName\":\"Fujita M\",\"firstName\":\"Morihisa\",\"lastName\":\"Fujita\",\"initials\":\"M\",\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Research Institute for Microbial Diseases and WPI Immunology Frontier Research Center, Osaka University, Suita, Osaka 565-0871, Japan; Key Laboratory of Carbohydrate Chemistry and Biotechnology, Ministry of Education, School of Biotechnology, Jiangnan University, Wuxi, Jiangsu 214122, China.\"}]}},{\"fullName\":\"Kinoshita T\",\"firstName\":\"Taroh\",\"lastName\":\"Kinoshita\",\"initials\":\"T\",\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Research Institute for Microbial Diseases and WPI Immunology Frontier Research Center, Osaka University, Suita, Osaka 565-0871, Japan.\"}]}},{\"fullName\":\"Yamaguchi Y\",\"firstName\":\"Yoshiki\",\"lastName\":\"Yamaguchi\",\"initials\":\"Y\",\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Structural Glycobiology Team, Systems Glycobiology Research Group, RIKEN-Max Planck Joint Research Center, RIKEN Global Research Cluster, 2-1 Hirosawa, Wako City, Saitama 351-0198, Japan. Electronic address: yyoshiki@riken.jp.\"}]}}]},\"authorIdList\":{\"authorId\":[{\"type\":\"ORCID\",\"value\":\"0000-0002-5470-3807\"},{\"type\":\"ORCID\",\"value\":\"0000-0003-1965-5405\"}]},\"dataLinksTagsList\":{\"dataLinkstag\":[\"altmetrics\",\"related_data\"]},\"journalInfo\":{\"issue\":\"20\",\"volume\":\"428\",\"journalIssueId\":2456956,\"dateOfPublication\":\"2016 Oct\",\"monthOfPublication\":10,\"yearOfPublication\":2016,\"printPublicationDate\":\"2016-10-01\",\"journal\":{\"title\":\"Journal of molecular biology\",\"medlineAbbreviation\":\"J Mol Biol\",\"nlmid\":\"2985088R\",\"isoabbreviation\":\"J Mol Biol\",\"issn\":\"0022-2836\",\"essn\":\"1089-8638\"}},\"pubYear\":\"2016\",\"pageInfo\":\"4087-4099\",\"abstractText\":\"The p24 family consists of four subfamilies (p24α, p24β, p24γ, and p24δ), and the proteins are thought to form hetero-oligomeric complexes for efficient transport of cargo proteins from the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi apparatus. The proteins possess a conserved luminal Golgi dynamics (GOLD) domain, whose functions are largely unknown. Here, we present structural and biochemical studies of p24β1 and p24δ1 GOLD domains. Use of GOLD domain-deleted mutants revealed that the GOLD domain of p24δ1 is required for proper p24 hetero-oligomeric complex formation and efficient transport of GPI-anchored proteins. The p24β1 and p24δ1 GOLD domains share a common β-sandwich fold with a characteristic intrasheet disulfide bond. The GOLD domain of p24δ1 crystallized as dimers, allowing the analysis of a homophilic interaction site. Surface plasmon resonance and solution NMR analyses revealed that p24β1 and p24δ1 GOLD domains interact weakly (K<sub>d</sub>= ~10<sup>-4</sup>M). Bi-protein titration provided interaction site maps. We propose that the heterophilic interaction of p24 GOLD domains contributes to the formation of the p24 hetero-oligomeric complex and to efficient cargo transport.\",\"affiliation\":\"Structural Glycobiology Team, Systems Glycobiology Research Group, RIKEN-Max Planck Joint Research Center, RIKEN Global Research Cluster, 2-1 Hirosawa, Wako City, Saitama 351-0198, Japan.\",\"publicationStatus\":\"ppublish\",\"language\":\"eng\",\"pubModel\":\"Print-Electronic\",\"pubTypeList\":{\"pubType\":[\"Journal Article\"]},\"grantsList\":{\"grant\":[{\"agency\":\"Osaka University\",\"orderIn\":0},{\"agency\":\"Research Institute for Microbial Diseases, Osaka University\",\"orderIn\":0},{\"agency\":\"Takeda Science Foundation\",\"orderIn\":0},{\"agency\":\"Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology\",\"orderIn\":0}]},\"meshHeadingList\":{\"meshHeading\":[{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Cell Line\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Golgi Apparatus\",\"meshQualifierList\":{\"meshQualifier\":[{\"abbreviation\":\"ME\",\"qualifierName\":\"metabolism\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"Y\"}]}},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Humans\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Nucleocytoplasmic Transport Proteins\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Membrane Proteins\",\"meshQualifierList\":{\"meshQualifier\":[{\"abbreviation\":\"ME\",\"qualifierName\":\"metabolism\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"Y\"},{\"abbreviation\":\"CH\",\"qualifierName\":\"chemistry\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"Y\"}]}},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Vesicular Transport Proteins\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Crystallography, X-Ray\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Magnetic Resonance Spectroscopy\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Surface Plasmon Resonance\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Protein Interaction Mapping\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Protein Conformation\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Protein Binding\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Protein Transport\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Models, Molecular\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"Y\",\"descriptorName\":\"Protein Multimerization\"}]},\"keywordList\":{\"keyword\":[\"GPI-anchored protein\",\"Protein transport\",\"Cargo Receptor\",\"P24 Family\",\"Gold Domain\"]},\"chemicalList\":{\"chemical\":[{\"name\":\"Membrane Proteins\",\"registryNumber\":\"0\"},{\"name\":\"Vesicular Transport Proteins\",\"registryNumber\":\"0\"},{\"name\":\"Nucleocytoplasmic Transport Proteins\",\"registryNumber\":\"0\"},{\"name\":\"TMED2 protein, human\",\"registryNumber\":\"0\"},{\"name\":\"TMED10 protein, human\",\"registryNumber\":\"0\"}]},\"subsetList\":{\"subset\":[{\"code\":\"IM\",\"name\":\"Index Medicus\"}]},\"fullTextUrlList\":{\"fullTextUrl\":[{\"availability\":\"Subscription required\",\"availabilityCode\":\"S\",\"documentStyle\":\"doi\",\"site\":\"DOI\",\"url\":\"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jmb.2016.08.023\"}]},\"isOpenAccess\":\"N\",\"inEPMC\":\"N\",\"inPMC\":\"N\",\"hasPDF\":\"N\",\"hasBook\":\"N\",\"hasSuppl\":\"N\",\"citedByCount\":39,\"hasData\":\"Y\",\"hasReferences\":\"Y\",\"hasTextMinedTerms\":\"Y\",\"hasDbCrossReferences\":\"Y\",\"dbCrossReferenceList\":{\"dbName\":[\"PDB\",\"UNIPROT\"]},\"hasLabsLinks\":\"Y\",\"hasEvaluations\":\"N\",\"authMan\":\"N\",\"epmcAuthMan\":\"N\",\"nihAuthMan\":\"N\",\"hasTMAccessionNumbers\":\"N\",\"dateOfCompletion\":\"2017-06-19\",\"dateOfCreation\":\"2016-08-30\",\"firstIndexDate\":\"2016-09-03\",\"dateOfRevision\":\"2021-12-04\",\"electronicPublicationDate\":\"2016-08-25\",\"firstPublicationDate\":\"2016-08-25\"}]}}","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_39","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"curl -L --fail --silent 'https://www.ebi.ac.uk/europepmc/webservices/rest/search?query=EXT_ID:19566487%20SRC:MED&format=json&pageSize=1&resultType=core'\"","aggregated_output":"{\"version\":\"6.9\",\"hitCount\":1,\"request\":{\"queryString\":\"EXT_ID:19566487 SRC:MED\",\"internalQuery\":\"EXT_ID:19566487 SRC:MED\",\"resultType\":\"CORE\",\"cursorMark\":\"*\",\"pageSize\":1,\"sort\":\"\",\"synonym\":false},\"resultList\":{\"result\":[{\"id\":\"19566487\",\"source\":\"MED\",\"pmid\":\"19566487\",\"doi\":\"10.1042/bc20080233\",\"title\":\"The p24 family and selective transport processes at the ER-Golgi interface.\",\"authorString\":\"Strating JR, Martens GJ.\",\"authorList\":{\"author\":[{\"fullName\":\"Strating JR\",\"firstName\":\"Jeroen R P M\",\"lastName\":\"Strating\",\"initials\":\"JR\",\"authorId\":{\"type\":\"ORCID\",\"value\":\"0000-0003-2509-5213\"},\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Department of Molecular Animal Physiology, Donders Centre for Neuroscience and Nijmegen Centre for Molecular Life Sciences (NCMLS), Faculty of Science, Radboud University, Nijmegen, The Netherlands.\"}]}},{\"fullName\":\"Martens GJ\",\"firstName\":\"Gerard J M\",\"lastName\":\"Martens\",\"initials\":\"GJ\"}]},\"authorIdList\":{\"authorId\":[{\"type\":\"ORCID\",\"value\":\"0000-0003-2509-5213\"}]},\"dataLinksTagsList\":{\"dataLinkstag\":[\"altmetrics\",\"related_data\"]},\"journalInfo\":{\"issue\":\"9\",\"volume\":\"101\",\"journalIssueId\":1632993,\"dateOfPublication\":\"2009 Sep\",\"monthOfPublication\":9,\"yearOfPublication\":2009,\"printPublicationDate\":\"2009-09-01\",\"journal\":{\"title\":\"Biology of the cell\",\"medlineAbbreviation\":\"Biol Cell\",\"isoabbreviation\":\"Biol Cell\",\"nlmid\":\"8108529\",\"essn\":\"1768-322X\",\"issn\":\"0248-4900\"}},\"pubYear\":\"2009\",\"pageInfo\":\"495-509\",\"abstractText\":\"The secretory pathway is of vital importance for eukaryotic cells and has a pivotal role in the synthesis, sorting, processing and secretion of a large variety of bioactive molecules involved in intercellular communication. One of the key processes in the secretory pathway concerns the transport of cargo proteins from the ER (endoplasmic reticulum) to the Golgi. Type-I transmembrane proteins of approximately 24 kDa are abundantly present in the membranes of the early secretory pathway, and bind the COPI and COPII coat complexes that cover vesicles travelling between the membranes. These p24 proteins are thought to play an important role in the selective transport processes at the ER-Golgi interface, although their exact functioning is still obscure. One model proposes that p24 proteins couple cargo selection in the lumen with vesicle coat recruitment in the cytosol. Alternatively, p24 proteins may furnish subcompartments of the secretory pathway with the correct subsets of machinery proteins. Here we review the current knowledge of the p24 proteins and the various roles proposed for the p24 family members.\",\"affiliation\":\"Department of Molecular Animal Physiology, Donders Centre for Neuroscience and Nijmegen Centre for Molecular Life Sciences (NCMLS), Faculty of Science, Radboud University, Nijmegen, The Netherlands.\",\"publicationStatus\":\"ppublish\",\"language\":\"eng\",\"pubModel\":\"Print\",\"pubTypeList\":{\"pubType\":[\"Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't\",\"Review\",\"Journal Article\"]},\"meshHeadingList\":{\"meshHeading\":[{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Endoplasmic Reticulum\",\"meshQualifierList\":{\"meshQualifier\":[{\"abbreviation\":\"ME\",\"qualifierName\":\"metabolism\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"Y\"}]}},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Golgi Apparatus\",\"meshQualifierList\":{\"meshQualifier\":[{\"abbreviation\":\"ME\",\"qualifierName\":\"metabolism\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"Y\"}]}},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Animals\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Humans\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Membrane Proteins\",\"meshQualifierList\":{\"meshQualifier\":[{\"abbreviation\":\"GE\",\"qualifierName\":\"genetics\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\"},{\"abbreviation\":\"ME\",\"qualifierName\":\"metabolism\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"Y\"},{\"abbreviation\":\"CH\",\"qualifierName\":\"chemistry\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\"}]}},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Protein Transport\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"Y\",\"descriptorName\":\"Multigene Family\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Secretory Pathway\"}]},\"chemicalList\":{\"chemical\":[{\"name\":\"Membrane Proteins\",\"registryNumber\":\"0\"}]},\"subsetList\":{\"subset\":[{\"code\":\"IM\",\"name\":\"Index Medicus\"}]},\"fullTextUrlList\":{\"fullTextUrl\":[{\"availability\":\"Free\",\"availabilityCode\":\"F\",\"documentStyle\":\"abs\",\"site\":\"www.biolcell.org\",\"url\":\"http://www.biolcell.org/boc/101/boc1010495.htm\"},{\"availability\":\"Subscription required\",\"availabilityCode\":\"S\",\"documentStyle\":\"html\",\"site\":\"www.biolcell.org\",\"url\":\"http://www.biolcell.org/boc/101/0495/boc1010495.htm\"},{\"availability\":\"Subscription required\",\"availabilityCode\":\"S\",\"documentStyle\":\"doi\",\"site\":\"DOI\",\"url\":\"https://doi.org/10.1042/BC20080233\"}]},\"isOpenAccess\":\"N\",\"inEPMC\":\"N\",\"inPMC\":\"N\",\"hasPDF\":\"N\",\"hasBook\":\"N\",\"hasSuppl\":\"N\",\"citedByCount\":151,\"hasData\":\"Y\",\"hasReferences\":\"Y\",\"hasTextMinedTerms\":\"Y\",\"hasDbCrossReferences\":\"N\",\"hasLabsLinks\":\"Y\",\"hasEvaluations\":\"N\",\"authMan\":\"N\",\"epmcAuthMan\":\"N\",\"nihAuthMan\":\"N\",\"hasTMAccessionNumbers\":\"N\",\"dateOfCompletion\":\"2009-09-09\",\"dateOfCreation\":\"2009-07-02\",\"firstIndexDate\":\"2009-09-10\",\"dateOfRevision\":\"2016-10-20\",\"firstPublicationDate\":\"2009-09-01\"}]}}","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
